<subSubSection id="C31E6567FFD6F6388CBF3CEDF910F6FA" pageId="18" pageNumber="76" type="conservation">
<paragraph id="8BBB36ECFFD6F6388CBF3CEDF910F6FA" blockId="18.[1438,2650,709,2520]" pageId="18" pageNumber="76">
<emphasis id="B970EAFEFFD6F6388CBF3CEDF959F689" bold="true" box="[1441,1788,2289,2322]" pageId="18" pageNumber="76">Status and Conservation.</emphasis>
Classified as Least Concern on The IUCN Red List. The Luzon Pygmy Fruit Bat is common and widespread and the most abundant fruit bat at elevations above 
<quantity id="4CFC9B09FFD6F6388F553D58F914F6FA" box="[1611,1713,2372,2401]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="18" pageNumber="76" unit="m" value="1000.0">1000 m</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
